Dear Dr. Caroline Emberson ,

Thank you for submitting your manuscript "Quantifying hidden exploitation: Dual method prevalence estimates of labour exploitation among domestic workers in the United Kingdom" to our journal. After careful assessment, we have made the decision not to consider your manuscript for publication in British Journal of Industrial Relations. In this case the paper is underdeveloped theoretically for a general IR journal like BJIR and is better suited perhaps to a more specific UK focused journal like IRJ or similar.
We appreciate you considering British Journal of Industrial Relations for the publication of your research.
Kind regards,
J. Ryan Lamare
British Journal of Industrial Relations
